(408666, 12391, 408657, 'adam', 8221, '', 1385106624, 'No need to worry brother Bukhtiar.\nAll air guns of Diana have "Barrel Droop". It means that in spite of full elevation adjustment from scope elevation turrent, the pellet hit the target Low at say 30 yards or whatever distance. This problem can be solved by different methods, like using droop compensator one piece mount, or Scope Shimming. \nWhat you have done is called scope shimming. Moderate scope shimming will not harm the scope or cause any other problem, just dont tighten the mount ring screws too much. Tighten with the supplied key moderately, not too loose and not death tight. It will not harm the scope.\n\nGood luck.', 1, 1, '111.88.43.224', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 0, 0),
